pageTitle: Cavani String Quartet | Chamber Music America
textBeforeTable: Sep2015     Winner Guarneri String Quartet Residency Award, Naumburg Chamber Music Award, Fischoff Coleman and Cleveland Quartet Fellowship Competition , CMA/ASCAP Award for Adventurous Programming. Recipient of six CMA Residency/Planning Partnership Grants. Appearancesat festivals and concert series in North America and Europe. Innovative programming includes The Beethoven & Brotherhood Project and COLLAGE: Music & Poetry. Critically acclaimed and inspiring educational programs available for ages K-12 : "Team Up with Music," "Outside The Box" M.A.P. (Music Art & Poetry). Faculty quartet-in-residence at the Cleveland Institute of Music. Recordings available on Azica, Albany, CIM and Pantheon labels. The Cleveland Institute of Music Residence Ensemble in info@cavani.org Management String
